						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Rājakēsarivarmaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Uḍaiyār Śrirājārājadē[va] who took the head of Vīra Pāṇḍya and destroyed the ships at Kāndaḷūr-sālai. Year: ⎯⎯</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete. Stone missing at the end. Records a gift of a lamp to the temple of Mahādēva at [Ūṟ]ṟattūr, for the merit of Surumāḍavichchiōsai Peṟṟāḷ, residing at Tiraṇi in Vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

